OB:
When attempting to create a FontRegistry instance in my application, I encounter a MissingResourceException. The code I use for this is as follows:

com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry() {
  FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I have a file named 'fonts.properties' in the 'com/company/product/' folder. However, when I use the following code instead:

com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry() {
  ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

No exception is thrown. Additionally, if I duplicate the FontRegistry class in my 'com.company.product' package, it works. I suspect there is a bug in the FontRegistry because it attempts to load the fonts resource bundle using the FontRegistry's class loader (refer to 'readResourceBundle(String)' method in FontRegistry).
